{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"a61e0261-8733-49a4-895e-4b8dcf6bbd85","content":"Here's a quick overview:\n\n**Templates:**\n- `dotnet new webapi` — ASP.NET Core Web API (most common)\n- `dotnet new webapiaot` — minimal API with Native AOT\n- `dotnet new web` — empty ASP.NET Core (bare minimum)\n\n**Authentication options (`--auth`):**\n| Option | Description |\n|---|---|\n| `None` | No auth (default) |\n| `IndividualB2C` | Azure AD B2C individual accounts |\n| `SingleOrg` | Single tenant Azure AD |\n| `MultiOrg` | Multi-tenant Azure AD |\n| `Windows` | Windows/Negotiate auth |\n\n**Example:**\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth SingleOrg --name MyApi\n```\n\nFor JWT bearer token auth without Azure AD, use `--auth None` and add `Microsoft.AspNetCore.Authentication.JwtBearer` manually.\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific configuration?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"0919cb10-584c-4457-a67f-7346821761f6","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - it's a straightforward informational question I can answer from my knowledge.","outputTokens":283},"id":"19edfdbc-4757-4515-81c5-0ce91abfc1c8","timestamp":"2026-04-08T00:50:09.954Z","parentId":"faac025b-2a06-4e99-98a2-dc46054cc8e5"}
